abstract_ssm: James McNaughton Hester served at New York University as Dean of the Graduate School of Arts and Science and Executive Dean of Arts and Sciences from 1960-1961, and as University President from 1962-1975. He went on to serve as rector of the United Nations University from 1975-1980. The collection contains drafts and supporting materials from speeches, presentations and articles given and written by Hester between 1960-1980, as well as photographs, awards and clippings from his tenure at NYU.
